# Redis Docker Quick Guide

## Start Redis
docker run --name local-redis -p 6379:6379 -d redis

## Connect to Redis CLI
docker exec -it local-redis redis-cli

## Basic Redis Commands
ping                    # Test connection (returns PONG)
set mykey "hello"      # Set a key
get mykey              # Get a key
keys *                 # Show all keys
del mykey              # Delete a key
flushall               # Delete all keys
exit                   # Exit CLI

## Container Management
docker ps              # Show running containers
docker stop local-redis    # Stop Redis
docker start local-redis   # Start Redis again
docker rm local-redis      # Remove container (when stopped)

## Notes
- Redis runs on port `6379`
- Container name is `local-redis`
- Data is lost when container is removed
- No password required for local use

## Quick Setup
1. Run the start command
2. Connect with CLI command
3. Test with `ping`
4. Start using Redis commands